<HEADLINE> Zhou Enlai Remembered In Hometown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province is
going to stage a series of activities in remembrance of late
Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai, including the unveiling a bronze
statute of the late leader and the opening of a museum housing his
personal belongings.
</P>
<P>
Related activities will continue through March 5, the date of
his birth.
</P>
<P>
Official remembrance ceremonies started today with a seminar on his
life, thinking and pursuits. Some 60 scholars attended the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The province is also expected to publish a series of books,
sponsor a film show and TV series on Zhou, and stage a calligraphy
and paintings exhibition in commemoration of the great Chinese
leader.  
</P>
</TEXT>
