<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Activities Held to Commemorate Cai Yuanpei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A forum to mark the 130th birth
anniversary of Cai Yuanpei, a renowned Chinese democratic
revolutionary, was held today in the north China coastal city of
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
People from all walks of life in the city attended the forum.
</P>
<P>
Cai, born in 1868 in Shaoxing, east China's Zhejiang Province, was
an educationist and scientist. He passed away in Hong Kong in 1940.
</P>
<P>
Late Chinese leader Mao Zedong spoke highly of Cai and praised
him as a member of the elite in the academic circle and an example
for later generations.
</P>
<P>
The ceremonies included speeches recalling Cai's deeds during
the May 4th Movement in 1919, his contributions to the
nation's scientific and educational endeavors, and his
theories on aesthetic education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
