<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norwegian Man Wins Crosscountry Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VEINNA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Thomsa Alsgaard won a
men's Nordic skiing World Cup cross-country race on Thursday in
Ramsau, Austria.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Norway's Marit Mikkelsplass led a 1-2 finish to win in
women's 10-kilometer classical style race.
</P>
<P>
Alsgaard, who also moved up into the top place in the World Cup
standigns after the victory, posted the winning time of 36
minutes, 22.6 seconds in the 15-kilometer classical style race.
</P>
<P>
Mika Myllyla of Finland clocked second 36:23.5 and his
courtryman Jari Isometsa was third, 18.8 seconds behind the
winner.
</P>
<P>
Bjorn Daehli, the Norwegian favorite who won five Olympics and
nine world titles, was fourth, 26.8 seconds behind his compatriot.
</P>
<P>
The defeat in the event dropped Daehli to second place in World
Cup standings with 542 points, four points behind Alsgaard.
</P>
<P>
The four-day series of races in this Austrian resort is the
dress rehearsal for next year's World Championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
