<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, January 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq Thursday refuted the statements of the
U.S. ambassador to the U.N. claiming that 95 percent of the
contracts of food and medicine within the second phase of
Iraq-U.N. oil-for-food program has been approved.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi News Agency quoted a spokesman for the Iraqi Trade
Ministry as saying that the real percentage was not more than 77
percent. (Iraq-US-UN)
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France Thursday welcomed the address delivered by
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami to the people of the United
States through the Cable News Network. (France-Iran-US)
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia's gross domestic product, industrial output
and retail trade grew by 1.2, 3.2 and 3.9 percent respectively in
1997, Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said Thursday.
(Russia-1997 Growth) 
</P>
