<HEADLINE> Workers Removing Snow from Road In North Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Local relief workers in Nagqu
County in the northern part of Tibet Autonomous Region, including
men of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, are working hard to
remove snow accumulations covered roads at 6,000 meters above sea
level.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 people have been marooned in Nima Township because
of snowstorms which have hit the area since last September.
</P>
<P>
According to the county magistrate in charge of the rescue and
relief work, crews are working 15 to 16 hours per day to clear
roads at the earliest possible date. However, he further noted
that progress is quite slow due to low temperatures and extremely
high accumulation of snow.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers have contributed tremendously to the efforts,
according to the magirstrate. Local herdsmen have frequently been
seen giving food and drinks to the soldiers, and young women have
also joined in the relief effort.  
</P>
</TEXT>
