<HEADLINE> Science-Technology Web Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Science and
Technology Network, the first of its kind in China, opened today
in Shanghai, the country's largest industrial center.
</P>
<P>
The web represents a major achievement in Shanghai's efforts
to transform the city into an information center.
</P>
<P>
The web, which features a high-speed data channels and the
transmission of high-quality audio and video signals, will also
operate 62 ATM exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-seven local institutions, including Fudan University,
Huashan Hospital and the Shanghai City Computer Institute,
contributed to the establishment of the network.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say the web will accelerate information
exchanges between Shanghai and other cities in the world.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
