<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Becomes Bulgaria's Biggest Trade Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
become the biggest trade partner of Bulgaria, with the bilateral
trade in 1996 accounting for 35 percent of the country's total
trade volume, reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This compares with the 30 percent of Bulgaria's trade with the
former Soviet republics and nine percent with other central and
east European countries in the year, said Eurostat, the EU's
Luxembourg-based statistical office.
</P>
<P>
The EU's trade with Bulgaria expanded vigorously between 1990
and 1995, with imports and exports rising by an annual average of
25.8 percent and 17.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to the Eurostat, Bulgaria's trade with its
traditional partners, particularly with the former Soviet
republics, has dropped since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Germany is Bulgaria's main EU trade partner, followed by Italy
and Greece, which accounted for 27.7 percent, 20.4 percent and
15.6 percent respectively of the EU's total trade with Bulgaria in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
