<HEADLINE> CIS Need to Undergo Radical Reforms: Kyrgyz President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyz President Askar
Akayevich Akayev has said the Commonwealth of Independent States
(CIS) need to undergo radical reforms.
</P>
<P>
The reforms, Akayev said, should build as soon as possible an
effective mechanism for economic cooperation within the CIS, so as
to provide a unified and solid foundation vital for its existence.
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyzstan's trade with other CIS members dropped 50 percent
last year from the 1995 figure which, said the president, was
worrisome for his country.
</P>
<P>
After Russia expressed its determination, at the latest CIS
summit, to strengthen links within the CIS, Akayev said, his
country hoped that this year would be a turning point in the CIS
integration process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
