<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac to Visit Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- At the invitation of Mozambican
President Joaquim Chissano, French President Jacques Chirac will
pay a visit to Mozambique from June 28 to 29.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first official visit by a French head of
state since Mozambique gained its independence in 1975.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today by an official from the French
Embassy in Maputo, the Mozambique News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"We are making preparations at present for Chirac's visit
along with our Mozambican colleagues," said the official who
didn't give his name.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Chirac's African tour will also include
Namibia and South Africa. 
</P>
