<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Angola today signed an agreement
on military cooperation with Congo (B), under which it will help
Congo (B) to train its army.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Joao de Matos, Angola's chief of
the General Staff, and his Congolese counterpart Yves Mutando
Mongonot on behalf of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Angola will train Congolese army soldiers
in the first phase, before turning to the navy and air force the
training of which are more complicated than that of the army.
</P>
<P>
Before the signing of the deal, the two chiefs of general
staff held a meeting on the Congolese army rebuilding with the
assistance of Angolan military experts.
</P>
<P>
Mongonot arrived in Luanda on Tuesday for a three-day visit
which is aimed to seek for military cooperation with Angola.
</P>
<P>
He is the highest ranking military officer from Congo (B) to
visit Angola since the end of armed conflicts in the central
African country. 
