<HEADLINE> Explosives Cache Found Near Dublin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Irish police said Thursday that
they had found a big cache of explosives near Dublin, capital of
Ireland, and four men had been arrested.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from Dublin, the cache of
explosives is clearly linked to the paramilitary conflict in
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said that "one-and-a-half tonnes of
explosives were found last night in Dublin" and It was believed
that there is paramilitary involvement in it.
</P>
<P>
Irish local media reported that at least one of the four
arrested men was linked to a new republican group named the 32
County Sovereignty Committee which opposes Sinn Fein's
participation in the Northern Ireland peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The incident is the latest twist in the recent escalation in
the Northern Irish conflict and situation there has been tense
following several paramilitary killings in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
