<HEADLINE> Over 480 Kilograms of Pure Heroin Seized in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 480.7 kilograms of
smuggled pure heroin was seized in eastern Turkey today,
semi-official Anatolia News agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish police stopped and searched a passenger bus, which
came from Baku, capital of Azerbaijan, at the Sarp Border Gate on
the Turkey-Georgia border, and found the heroin in 470 parcels
hidden in the bus.
</P>
<P>
The police also detained the driver of the bus, according to
the news agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a key transit route of drugs to Europe from the area
bordering Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police
seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, or 40 percent of the world's total
haul, 12.3 tonnes of hashish, 233 kilograms of opium, 13
kilograms of cocaine and 1,157 kilograms of base
morphine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
