<HEADLINE> Marshall Island, Mozambique, Sweden pay Full Assessed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 8 (xinhua) -- Marshall Island,
Mozambique and Sweden had paid in full their assessed contribution
to the regular budget of the United Nations for 1998, UN spokesman
Juan Carlos Brandit announced today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Marshall Island paid 10,516 U.S dollars,
Mozambique 21,032 and Sweden 11,557,384.
</P>
<P>
Finland is the first member state to pay in full its assessed
contribution to the regular budget of the United Nations for
1998, who paid 5,6 million dollars Monday. Denmark is the
second, who paid 7,224,679 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding contribution to the United Nations is over
3.1 billion U.S. dollars. Of that amount, roughly 1.6 billion is
for the regular budget, and over 1.5 billion for peacekeeping,
said the spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
