<HEADLINE> High Concentration of Salt Water Found in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Urban Development,
Mines and Energy Bureau of Ethiopia's Somali Region has announced
that there is high concentration of salt water in four areas of
the region.
</P>
<P>
The salt water takes two to three days to solidify under the
sun and the inhabitants have been producing salt in traditional
ways, the Ethiopian News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the Ethiopian Standardization Authority has
conducted a study on the substance and proved that it contains 96
percent sodium chloride including calcium and magnesium.
</P>
<P>
Although the salt water has no iodine, the United Nations
Children's Fund has promised to donate machineries that
will enable to iodize the salt deposit in the areas, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
