<HEADLINE> More Company Failures Seen In Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) - Britain faces an increase in the
number of company collapses because of high interest rates and
falling economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Although business failures last year were at their lowest
level, a rise would reverse the trend of the past 5 years, said
leading accountants KPMG.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures released on Thursday by the
firm, the number of company receiverships fell last year to 1181
-a 15 percent dip on the previous year's total.
</P>
<P>
KPMG's head of corporate recovery Mike Wheeler said: "The eight
to 10-year business cycle in Britain suggests that 1998 will mark
the trough in the level of business failures."
</P>
<P>
"We are poised for an upturn in company collapses after that,"
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
