<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin on Thursday called on troops to be on the alert
against Chechen terrorist attacks, but disagreed to stage
preventive blows on Chechnya's terrorist bases.
</P>
<P>
Referring to a Chechen raid on a Russian tank unit in late
December last year, Chernomyrdin stressed that the "power" bodies,
including army, police and security, "must not permit such actions
to be performed on our territory."
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin noted that the situation in the breakaway republic
and on its border with adjacent republics is difficult because
Chechen militants have repeatedly made brazen attacks on Russian
troops.
</P>
<P>
However, he resolutely stood against the pronouncements of
Interior Minister Anatoly Kilikov concerning the "preventive
blows" on the Chechen territory and proposed "a preventive bang"
on the negotiating table instead.
</P>
<P>
The premier noted that Russia is "conducting a policy towards
reaching agreements." "We are constantly negotiating with the
authorities of the Chechen republic," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin meanwhile emphasized that Cabinet members have no
right to express their own opinions on behalf of the government.
</P>
