<HEADLINE> Chinese Chief of General Staff on Defense Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese armed forces must
fully understand the profound changes in the world strategic
patterns and the trends in worldwide military development in order
to improve the quality of the Chinese army.
</P>
<P>
General Fu Quanyou, member of the Central Military Commission
and Chief of General Staff, made the remarks today at a
military conference in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The army must condense its power and boost morale with
cross-century strategic goals, said Fu.
</P>
<P>
The army should proceed under the guidance of Mao Zedong's
military thinking, Deng Xiaoping's theories on defense
modernization during the new period, and Jiang Zemin's
instructions on related issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
The army should focus its efforts on increasing combat
effectiveness, improving the quality of its men and developing
hi-tech equipment, according to the general.
</P>
<P>
The army should build a highly efficient structure and be fully
prepared to face challenges in worldwide military development in
order to gain a strategic advantage in the next century, said Fu.
</P>
