<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua
today called for the Chinese statistical departments to place
priority on accuracy and accelerate restructuring of the nation's
statistical system.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier made the call during a meeting with
participants at a national conference on statistical work.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of achieving overall improvement in
the quality of the statistical work.
</P>
