Prodi told a press conference at the airport at the end of his
two-day official visit to the South Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Italy agreed to contribute to the proposed Ganges barrage
project of Bangladesh to harness the river for irrigation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said his country would also help Bangladesh set up a leather
and footwear designing and fashion center in Dhaka, capital of
Bangladesh.
The Italian prime minister congratulated his Bangladeshi
counterpart, Sheikh Hasina, on the signing of a peace agreement
between the Bangladeshi government and the Chittagong Hill Tracts
last December, and the Ganges water sharing treaty in 1996 with
countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
