the whole region, Prodi said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the same press conference, Hasina said Bangladesh
and Italy can further cooperate in trade, investment and other
economic fields for mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi prime minister said she and Prodi discussed
ways of increasing trade and investment flows between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that it (the visit) will further contribute to
strengthening relations between Bangladesh and Italy, particularly
in the field of trade and foreign investment," she said.
</P>
<P>
Prodi arrived here on Thursday evening after a three-day visit
to India. This was the first visit by an Italian head of
government to Bangladesh since the two countries established
diplomatic relations 25 years ago.  
