He told the king that he had held talks with Moroccan Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Adbellatif Filali on reinforcement
of bilateral relations and overall cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that China and Morocco have had similar
experience over the past centuries and also have the similar tasks
to accomplish, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
King Hassan II said he agreed that China and Morocco had
similar unhappy experiences in the past.
</P>
<P>
The king said that only good will and patience will allow
Morocco to solve the problems which came down from the past.
</P>
<P>
Qian highly praised Morocco's economic achievements and its
role in helping maintain regional stability.
</P>
<P>
The king briefed Qian on the situation in the Mediterranean
region and Africa and hoped the economic and trade cooperation
between Morocco and China could develop smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China is ready to receive the king at any moment
convenient for him to visit.
</P>
<P>
Filali was present at Thursday's meeting. 
