and policies set forth at the 15th CPC National Congress held in
September 1997, there are many arduous tasks ahead in reform,
economic development and social stability, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Last year's agricultural production was a good one following
two years of consecutive good harvests, paving the way for the
country's economic growth and social stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiang attributed the good harvests to concerted efforts by
farmers under the leadership of Party committees and governments
at all levels as well as support from other trades. He also
extended cordial greetings to those working in the agricultural
industry on behalf of the CPC Central Committee and the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
It is essential to guard against laxity after good harvests and
attach more importance to studying the changing situation and new
problems, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding problems in rural areas now include weak sales in
farm produce, a drop in prices and slower growth in farmers'
income, Jiang said, adding that they will hamper social stability
if the country fails to find a timely and effective solution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Outlines Tasks for Agriculture, Rural Work in 1998 (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A key to doing a good job in rural areas is to stabilize all
policies, especially the Party's policies on the land-contract
system, grain purchases and alleviation of farmers' burdens, the
Party general secretary said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a breakthrough must be made in optimizing the
rural economic structure, raising farmers' incomes and maintaining
a balanced development between rural capital construction and
ecological protection.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said a welcome trend is the building of the joint stock
cooperative system in collective enterprises at the township
level. The system will be operated in a down-to-earth manner to
make it more popular among the masses, he said.
</P>
<P>
Implementation of the system should be based on the principle
of seeking truth from facts and be carried out in the light of
conditions of different areas. "There is no need to rush headlong
into mass action," he said. "Collective assets should not be
allowed to become the personal assets of a tiny number of people,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
The Party general secretary called on leading officials at all
levels to effectively improve their work styles and to go deeper
into the grassroots level to investigate and study new problems.
</P>
<P>
Leaders at the county level were urged to meet the masses of
farmers and help them solve concrete problems, render all kinds of
services and provide them with new ways to get well-to-do.
</P>
<P>
Many management and technical people with varied educational
backgrounds will be trained to meet the needs of rural development
through adjusting the existing educational structure in rural
areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
The democratic electoral system practiced in rural villages
will continue to improve, he said. Village affairs management and
accounts should be made public, he said, and democratic
supervision over rural officials should be tightened.
</P>
</TEXT>
