<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Outlines Tasks for Agriculture, Rural Work in 1998 (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Under the new blueprint, the per-capita net income of farmers
will be raised by 5 percent, and the rural population living below
the poverty line will be reduced by more than 10 million in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The accomplishment of the above tasks will lay a solid
foundation for reaching the goal of reaping an annual grain output
of 500 million tons, ensuring that farmers living a comfortable
life, and guaranteeing enough food and clothing for people living
in poor areas by the end of the century, according to a document
released at the conference.
</P>
<P>
General guidelines formulated at the conference called for
upholding the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and
implementing the policies worked out at the 15th National Congress
of the CPC in an all-round manner.
</P>
<P>
The conference stressed steady progress in agricultural work,
called for continuing to stabilize and consolidate the status of
agriculture as the base of all sectors and implementing the basic
policies of the CPC in rural areas, as well as stabilizing the
gross output of farm produce and maintaining social order in rural
areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Guiding Principles For Agriculture in 1998 (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Further stabilize and strengthen agriculture as the
foundation of the national economy, and maintain a sustainable and
steady growth of agriculture;
</P>
<P>
-- Resolutely stabilize and implement the Party's basic rural
policies, and take effective measures to protect and bring
farmers' initiative into full play;
</P>
<P>
-- Act promptly to adjust and optimize the industrial structure
in rural areas and the product mix in a bid to improve the quality
and efficiency of the farming sector as a whole;
</P>
<P>
-- Vigorously intensify the essential factors to increase
agricultural production and improve its efficiency, and to raise
agriculture's comprehensive production capacity;
</P>
<P>
-- Take positive and proper measures to step up rural reforms
and inject new vitality into agriculture and the rural economy;
</P>
<P>
-- Improve the agricultural infrastructure and balance economic
and social development;
</P>
<P>
The conference held that after three consecutive years' good
harvests, sustainable and steady agricultural growth can be scored
as long as top priority is given to agriculture in all economic
work and the Party's basic rural policies are followed.
</P>
<P>
Measures must be taken to ensure that attention to agriculture
will not be shifted elsewhere, efforts will not be relaxed and
investment will not be reduced. In addition, work must be done to
improve the eco-system and production conditions, and to promote
rapid progress and the widespread application of agricultural
scientific and technological revolution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Guiding Principles For Agriculture In 1998 (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Good or poor agricultural harvests rely heavily on farmers'
initiative, which in turn hinges on the Party's rural
policies. So, governments at all levels must be held accountable
to carrying out Party policies, including the household-based
contract responsibility system and policies to ease the farmers'
financial burdens and purchase any amount of grain from farmers at
protective prices.
</P>
<P>
China is experiencing a shift from a self-sufficient farming
sector to a commodity-oriented one and from a traditional farming
sector to a modern one. Therefore, efforts should be made to
improve the agricultural structure to adapt to a socialist
market economy. The farm product processing industry should be
developed and made into a new rural economic growth area, as well
as a pillar industry of China's economy.
</P>
<P>
In restructuring the rural industrial structure, it is
essential to improve to market analyses and prediction, and
provide timely and accurate market information for farmers.
</P>
<P>
Attention should be focused on cultivating country fairs and
farm produce wholesale markets, and on enlivening distribution.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, positive and proper measures should be taken to
promote market-oriented agricultural industrialization, and to
foster and support leading enterprises, which will serve as
examples in rural areas in opening up markets, guiding production,
and participating in sales.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Guiding Principles for Agriculture In 1998 (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agricultural infrastructure remains a weak link and
vulnerable to natural disasters, with inadequate applications of
science and technology to agriculture. A step forward for
agriculture will require the intensification of various production
factors and increase agriculture's comprehensive production
capacity.
</P>
<P>
Leaders at all levels must take agro-sciences as the primary
productive force, gradually promote farm mechanization and make a
greater effort to fight poverty. Furthermore, governments and
departments at all levels should continue to carry out
preferential policies for and increase investment in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, efforts should also be made to promote rural reforms,
especially to solve outstanding problems that hinder the
development of productivity. However, these reforms should be
tried out before widespread application.
</P>
<P>
Focuses should be placed on building the Party's organizations at
the village level to promote a democratic system characterized by
an open administration and democratic management.
</P>
<P>
The household contract responsibility system introduced in the
early 1980s has brought farmers' initiative in production into
full play. A sound democratic system could arouse the farmers'
political enthusiasm and this in turn will promote economic and
social prosperity in rural areas, the conference said.
</P>
</TEXT>
