<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CSA to Punish Swimmer Yuan Yuan and Coach Zhou Zhewen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Swimming Association
(CSA) will punish swimmer Yuan Yuan and coach Zhou Zhewen who both
were involved taking a banned drug into Australia, said the
Chinese delegation leader Shi Tianshu on Firday night.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese delegation shall deprive these two people of the
right to participate in the current world championships," Shi
said. "Further action will be taken in accordance with the rules
and regulations of the Chinese Swimming Association, and the FINA
will be duly informed of the result."
</P>
<P>
In a routine baggage check at the Sydney Airport, Yuan was
found to have in her bag a suspicious substance which a laboratory
in Sydney confirmed on Friday is growth hormone, a drug usually
used to cure children slow growth but banned in sports.
</P>
<P>
"According to swimming coach Zhou Zhewen, before they came here
someone asked him to take the substance over here. This is their
individual behavior and they will be responsible for all the
consequences thus arising," Shi said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation leader reaffirmed CSA's stand at
fighting performance-enhancing drugs.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Swimming Association insists on the policy of
strick prohibition, strick examination and strict sanction," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The number of drug tests that CSA conducted among its swimmers
in 1997 can reflect the Chinese swimming body's determination to
fight against doping, Shi noted.
</P>
<P>
"Last year we conducted over 600 tests, including 460
out-of-competition checks, on Chinese swimmers and none turned out
positive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The world swimming ruling body FINA did 104 flight tests on
Chinese swimmers last year and all of these tests were negative,
the team leader added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, FINA secretary general Gunnar Werner said that FINA
Bureau won't punish Yuan and Zhou pending its doping penal's
hearing on this issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
