<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draw Held for HK's Lunar New Year Soccer Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Luck turned in favor of the
Hong Kong soccer team's new Brazilian coach Sebastiao Pereira
Araujo as he obtained on Friday what he had expected -- playing
the Chilean team on the opening day of the coming Carlsberg Cup
Lunar New Year soccer tournament here.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is to play Chile while Iran plays Nigeria on January
28. The losers of the first two matches will vie for the third
place while the winners on the opening day will clash each other
for the championship trophy on January 31.
</P>
<P>
Chile, Iran and Nigeria have all qualified for the World Cup
finals in June this year in France.
</P>
<P>
The organizers felt happy and settled after receiving
confirmation from the three visiting teams for participation.
"With three World Cup finals sides here, this year's tournament
could be expected to be the best ever held in Hong Kong," a
spokesman for the organizers said at the lots-drawing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Araujo admitted before the lots were drawn that he would prefer
playing Chile in the Hong Kong team's first match at the two-day
event. "I think the Chileans are not as physically strong as the
Nigerians. If we could meet them first, we'd have more chance for
the final," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Football Association had received players' lists
from the Iranian and Chilean football associations -- 30 for Iran
and 25 for Chile. But their playing squads would be finalized to
a size of about 22 players each.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong League Eleven side is said to be formed after the
coming Guangdong-Hong Kong Cup, with local players picked up from
the current Hong Kong line-up and several foreign players now
playing in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
