<HEADLINE> Singapore Nabs 148 Suspected Drug Offenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 9 (Xinhua) -- In a continuing effort to
clear the streets of drug pushers and abusers, Singapore narcotics
officers nabbed 148 suspected drug offenders in a 39-hour
island-wide operation, the Central Narcotics Bureau (CNB) said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Of those arrested in the raid, which started early on
Wednesday, 81 were tested positive for narcotic drugs, 19 for
cannabis, eight for amphetamine and one for both narcotic drugs
and amphetamine, the CNB said.
</P>
<P>
It said the 109 people tested positive for controlled drugs
were aged between 15 and 48 years.
</P>
<P>
The CNB also seized a total of nine sachets and 72 straws of
heroin and 120 "Upjohn" tablets during the raid.  
</P>
</TEXT>
