<HEADLINE> Armed Men Rob Bank in Malaysia's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Four men, each of them
carrying a pistol, robbed a bank in the capital city Friday and
escaped with 100,000 ringgit (about 21,900 U.S. dollars) cash from
the bank, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
The four men were wearing crash helmets that covered their
faces when they went into the Hong Leong Bank in Jalan Klang Lama,
and they left in a car, Bernama said, quoting a senior police
officer.
</P>
<P>
There were between 20 and 30 customers in the bank when the
robbery took place but no one was injured, the police officer
said.  
