<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vaccine Curing Cancer Ready in 3-5 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- A vaccine which may lead to a
cure of cancer will be ready in three to five years, the Cyprus
Weekly magazine said today.
</P>
<P>
"It will take three to five years to see whether the vaccine is
effective, because patients injected with it will initially be in
remission," Greek Australian immunologist Vasso Apostolopoulou on
a four-day visit to Cyprus was quoted as saying by the Weekly.
</P>
<P>
Apostolopoulou, a woman researcher of the Austin Research
Institute in Melbourne, Australia, is currently working in the
third of the four testing phases of the vaccine, a potential
major breakthrough in cancer research.
</P>
<P>
At this period, the vaccine will be tested on 1,000 women in
Greece, including Cypriots, in their early stage of breast cancer
to see if it kills the cell of cancer.
</P>
<P>
The vaccine made up of synthetic mucin found in cancer and
synthetic sugar is used to kill the mucin in cancer and help the
human immune system produce antibodies T-lymphocytes, which can
destroy the disease.
</P>
<P>
Apostolopoulou has verified through her first two tests of the
vaccine on human bodies that the vaccine has no side effects on
human being and that the human immune system responds to it
positively, which are exactly what she has hoped for, the Weekly
magazine said.
</P>
<P>
In the fourth phase, she will test the vaccine on individuals
with a high risk of developing cancer due to hereditary factors,
and then as a preventive on children, according to the Weekly.
</P>
<P>
She expressed optimism that the vaccine will become an
effective weapon against cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
