<HEADLINE> Balloonist Rutan Launches Round-the-world Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 9 (Xinhua) -- American balloonist Dick
Rutan and co-pilot David Melton rose into the dawn sky over
Albuquerque, New Mexico, early Friday, beginning to circle the
globe non-stop in a hot-air balloon.
</P>
<P>
The "Global Hilton" was launched at 6:19 a.m. (1319 GMT), three
days after Rutan and Melton's original liftoff was postponed
because of shifting wind patterns over the Atlantic Ocean.
</P>
<P>
It is the third liftoff of a hot air/helium balloon since
December 31, when American Steve Fossett's took off from Saint
Louis in his unpressurized "Solo Spirit," only to be forced to
land over Russia four days later due to technical problems.
</P>
