<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cultural Activities in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Cultural activities in six major
cities in east China's Fujian Province have been expanding in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
City governments of Xiamen, Quanzhou, Zhangzhou, Putian, Ningde
and Fuzhou have spent 530 million yuan to set up more than 30
cultural facilities like museums, libraries, theaters and art
centers. Also, 90 similar facilities have been set up in their
rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Culture departments in these cities have provided a number of photo
and painting exhibitions, and many art troupes and folk artists
have given performances of acrobatics, puppet, ethnic songs and
danced, and local operas.
</P>
<P>
A group of 218 experts in the cities visited 18 countries and
regions for cultural exchange programs last year, and 103 artists
came to visit them from eight countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the cities in 1997 sent 95 artists to give
performances in Taiwan, and received five groups of 71
artists from Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
