<HEADLINE> British Trade Chief to Visit Hong Kong Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The president of the British
Board of Trade is to pay a four-day visit to the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) next week, the first British
high-level trade mission to Hong Kong since its return to China on
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Margaret Beckett is scheduled to open the British Council's
Education Festival, visit the new airport, have several briefings
with senior SAR officials and address leading business figures at
a lunch to be hosted by the British Chamber of Commerce, the
British Consulate-General said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Beckett reportedly said earlier: "I am delighted to be visiting
Hong Kong just over six months after the handover. The message I
am taking to Hong Kong is that Britain and British business is
committed to a major business presence, building on our existing
very strong links."
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong is extremely important, not just because of its own
dynamic economy, but as a gateway for business into China," she
said, noting that China including Hong Kong as its part is a very
important market for Britain both now and in the medium and long
term.
</P>
<P>
Beckett is scheduled to arrive here on January 15 from her
four-day trip to Beijing and she will proceed to Pakistan on
January 18.  
</P>
