<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Reports Increase in Passenger Flow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
said on Friday that its passenger flow and cargo shipment
increased remarkably in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The total number of passengers using the airport in 1997 added
up to 1.952 million, up 50 percent from 1996 while its cargo
shipment reached 45,540 tons, up 82 percent.
</P>
<P>
The airport said in a press release that total landings and
takeoffs at the airport, which was inaugurated in November 1995,
grew to more than 19,800 in 1997, up 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the amount of mail it handled dropped a little from
1996, reaching 156 tons.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Air Macao carried 989,553 passengers last year, a
rise of 49 percent. The air company's cargo transportation went up
by 42.8 percent from 1996 to hit 10,920 tons.
</P>
<P>
Air Macao plans to add some charter service this year,
including flights to Singapore, Malaysia and Japan. It also plans
to have more regular flights to Thailand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
