<HEADLINE> Two Nepalese Men Arrested in HK for Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs officers
arrested two Nepalese men at the Hong Kong International Airport
Thursday night and confiscated from them a total of 12.68
kilograms of cannabis resin, the Government Information Service
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
At about 9:30 PM Thursday, customs officers intercepted a
Nepalese man, who had just arrived in Hong Kong from Nepal, for
examination.
</P>
<P>
As a result, 4.68 kilograms of cannabis resin were found
concealed in the inner linings of the suitcase the 32-year-old man
was carrying.
</P>
<P>
About an hour later, Customs officers found another Nepalese
man, aged 26, arriving in Hong Kong by the same flight, in
possession of eight kilograms of cannabis resin during baggage
examination.
</P>
<P>
The seized drug was similarly concealed in the inner linings of
the suitcase he was carrying. The two men will appear in a
magistracy Saturday, on charges of trafficking in a dangerous
drug.  
</P>
</TEXT>
