<HEADLINE> Construction of Expressway Begins in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a 135.5-km
expressway from Luoyang to Sanmenxia cities in central China's
Henan province started Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will be part of China's east-west trunk road to
link the coastal city of Lianyungang in the east to Horgas in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in the northwest.
</P>
<P>
The road section in Henan will involve an investment of 4.2
billion yuan (506 million U.S. dollars), of which 470 million
U.S. dollars will be loans from the World Bank. It will be
completed in 44 months.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, expressways in the province
now total 400 kilometers in length. 
</P>
