<HEADLINE> China to Attend World's Largest Toy Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China will have the largest
exhibition team for the 1998 Spielwarenmesse International Toy
Fair to be in Nurnberg, Germany, in February.
</P>
<P>
According to Gerd Bise, chairman of the fair's executive board,
221 manufacturers from Hong Kong together with 24 Chinese mainland
counterparts have signed up for this year's Nurnberg toy fair, the
largest of its kind.
</P>
<P>
As the fair's most important buyer in Asia for many years,
China will send a purchase group of 320 professionals to the fair,
scheduled for Feb. 5-11, Bise said today.
</P>
<P>
It's unthinkable not to have China take part in the world's toy
market, Bise said, adding that China both as producer and consumer
is significant to the industry.
</P>
<P>
Bise said that China produces more than 50 percent of the
world's toys.
</P>
<P>
The Nurnberg Toy Fair was first held in 1950, and has become
one of the most important toy fairs in the world.
</P>
<P>
This year's fair, with a space of 144,000 square meters, will
attract about 300 manufacturers from 54 countries and 50,000
buyers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
