<HEADLINE> State Council Passes Draft Law on Land Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, China's top
administrative body, held the 65th meeting of its Executive
Committee today and passed a draft of the revised Law on Land
Management in principle.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the revised law is to reinforce land
management and safeguard socialist public ownership of the
nation's land in order to protect, properly develop and use
related resources, especially cultivated areas.
</P>
<P>
The draft of the revised law, which includes six chapters and
articles, contains stipulations regarding the principles of land
management, ownership and land-use rights, and the protection of
related resources, as well as related responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
Following further revisions, the draft will be submitted to the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress for
examination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
