<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen's Environmentally-friendly Autoworks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen
Co. Ltd., a Sino-German joint venture, has become the first
environmentally-friendly enterprise in China's automotive industry.
</P>
<P>
It was recently granted an ISO14000 certificate for
environmental management by the National Environmental Management
System's Examination Center.
</P>
<P>
The carmaker, one of the country's 500 best Sino-foreign joint
ventures, has now taken the lead in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
It has placed much attention on the design and manufacturing of
cars to reduce pollution.
</P>
<P>
Its "Santana 2000" series has been called a new generation of
environmentally-friendly cars by local experts.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of 1997, the company produced 211,700
cars, up 15.4 percent from the same 1996 period.  
