<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Tajikistan Defense Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian held talks today with Sherali Khairullaev, his Tajikistan
counterpart, and said that China is fully prepared to cooperate
Tajikistan in the realm of military training and logistics.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also State Councillor and vice-chairman of China's Central
Military Commission, said that China pursues an independent
foreign policy of peace and will not form alliances with any major
power or group of states.
</P>
<P>
Ideological and social systems should not be the criteria used
in state-to-state relations and China opposes any country
attempting to interfere in the internal affairs of another nation
under the pretext of nationality, religion and human rights, said
Chi.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China and Tajikistan are close and
friendly neighbors which have witnessed sustained and healthy
growth of bilateral relations since the two nations forged
diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
He noted that relations between the armed forces of China and
Tajikistan constitute an important aspect of ties and there are
broad prospects for collaboration between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Chi emphasized that China is fully prepared to work with
Tajikistan to establish a stable, mutually beneficial and
good-neighbor relationship.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the visiting delegation on the situation in
China and modernization of the Chinese army.
</P>
<P>
Khairullaev said that China is an important neighbor and
stressed that the development of friendly bilateral ties will not
only serve the interests of the two peoples, but will also promote
peace and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Frequent exchange of visits between leaders of the two nations
and their armed forces have greatly promoted bilateral relations,
said Khairullaev, adding that his country will continue to work
with China to enhance bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Chi also presided over a welcoming ceremony in honor of
Khairullaev, who arrived earlier today on an official goodwill
visit to China as guest of the Chinese Defense Minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
