<HEADLINE> Hong Kong: Ideal Regional Licensing Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Geographic advantages, a
strong economic foundation and a wealth of management personnel
have made Hong Kong an ideal regional partner in licensing, a
senior member of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC)
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regional licensing seminar, TDC Deputy Executive
Director Frederick Lam noted that the licensing industry worldwide
has an annual business turnover of 102 billion U.S. dollars and a
lot of international licensers and holders of top-notch brands
are targeting at the opportunities in the Asian-Pacific region
and China.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is well equipped to be a regional base for
international firms and enterprises to develop their businesses in
Asia, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is recognized as the freest economy in the world,
offering an open and fair trading environment; it is also the most
service-oriented economy in the world, providing all-round
services in financing, trading, telecommunications,
transportation, sourcing, licensing and product design to China's
inland areas and the region, said Lam.
</P>
<P>
The seminar entitled "Hong Kong: Your Regional Licensing
Partner" is part of a series of measures by the TDC to promote
Hong Kong as a global middle man for those wishing to expand their
business network.
</P>
<P>
It was held in conjunction with the Hong Kong Toys and Games
Fair '98 at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Licensing professionals from the United States, China's inland
areas and Hong Kong attended the meeting.  
</P>
