Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin met with for the first
time Thursday representatives of jobless people, who urged him to
make a gesture by providing financial aid to the unemployed. While
expressing understanding of the demands of the jobless, Jospin
ordered with a threatening tone the protesters to end their
occupation of government agencies and other forms of protest.
</P>
<P>
-- Algeria Thursday agreed to a proposal by the European Union
(EU) to send a delegation to Algiers, on the condition that the
mission of the delegation is focused on discussion over cooperation
in fighting terrorism. The wave of killings in the Ouarsenis
mountains in western Algeria pushed the EU to decide to help put an
end to terrorism in Algeria, which has earlier rejected an EU
proposal to provide aid to victims of the massacres.
</P>
