Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The French Interior Ministry said in a report on 1997 that
15,791 violent incidents took place in French cities last year,
while the number of large-scale violence, such as the riot which
took place on New Year's eve in Strasbourg, has diminished since
1993. Seven French cities experienced riots in 1997, while police
were subjected to grave physical attacks in 36 cities.
</P>
<P>
-- The French Minister of National Education Claude Allegre has
launched a large operation to investigate what the schoolchildren
and high school students want to learn. His ministry has sent 3
million questionnaires to schools across the country asking teachers
pupils and students to answer these questions before January 29. A
special commission headed by college professors has also been set up
to analyze the result of the investigation. 
