<HEADLINE> China Sets Guiding Principles For Agriculture in 1998 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Greater effort must be made in
six areas to accomplish the goals for agriculture in 1998 set by
the Central Rural Work Conference of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), which ended here today.
</P>
<P>
-- Further stabilize and strengthen agriculture as the
foundation of the national economy, and maintain a sustainable and
steady growth of agriculture;
</P>
<P>
-- Keep the Party's basic rural policies stable, and take
effective measures to protect and bring farmers' initiative into
full play;
</P>
<P>
-- Act promptly to adjust and optimize the industrial structure
in rural areas and the product mix in a bid to improve the quality
and efficiency of the farming sector as a whole;
</P>
<P>
-- Vigorously intensify the essential factors to increase
agricultural production and improve its efficiency, and to raise
agriculture's comprehensive production capacity;
</P>
<P>
-- Take positive and proper measures to step up rural reforms
and inject new vitality into agriculture and the rural economy;
</P>
<P>
-- Improve the agricultural infrastructure and balance economic
and social development;
</P>
<P>
The conference held that after three consecutive years' of good
harvests, sustainable and steady agricultural growth can be
achieved as long as top priority is given to agriculture in all
economic work and the Party's basic rural policies are
followed.
</P>
<P>
Measures must be taken to ensure that attention to agriculture
will not be shifted elsewhere, efforts will not be relaxed and
investment will not be reduced. In addition, work must be done to
improve the eco-system and production conditions, and to promote
rapid progress and the widespread application of agricultural
scientific and technological revolution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
