<HEADLINE> Nearly 200,000 More Germans Lose Jobs in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Germany's unemployed population
rose by nearly 200,000 to 4,521,600 in December, said the
Nuremberg-based Federal Labour Office Friday.
</P>
<P>
The increase surpassed the figure of 130,000 to 180,000 which
had earlier been projected by labor market experts.
</P>
<P>
The December unemployment rate rose by 0.5 percentage points to
11.8 percent from the November's.
</P>
<P>
Bernhard Jagoda, president of the office, attributed the rise
in unemployment to seasonal factors. 
</P>
