<HEADLINE> Shantou City Smashes 117 Drug Trafficking Gangs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Shantou City in south China's
Guangdong Province has made remarkable progress with an anti-drug
campaign by smashing 117 gangs engaged in trafficking and sale in
the past year.
</P>
<P>
As one of the special economic zones in China, Shantou City is
a harbor town with a long coast. To combat drug trafficking, the
Shantou government launched anti-drug campaigns involving Customs,
railway, frontier guard, civil aviation, administration of
industry and commerce.
</P>
<P>
From April to December of 1997, the city had cleared up 1,458
drug cases and arrested 2,294 drug traffickers and addicts.
</P>
<P>
A city official said the police also seized about 20 kilograms
of heroin, 10.46 kilograms of "ice" and 54 kilograms of ephidrine
as well as more than one million yuan in drug funds. 
</P>
