<HEADLINE> British PM Arrives in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
arrived here Friday on a five-day visit to Japan for talks with
Japanese political and business leaders.
</P>
<P>
During his first visit to Japan since assuming the premiership
last May, Blair is expected to hold talks with his Japanese
counterpart Ryutaro Hashimoto to discuss how to promote bilateral
relations through a joint vision toward the 21st century, Japanese
Foreign Ministry officials said.
</P>
<P>
Blair will also have an audience with Japanese Emperor Akihito
and Empress Michiko and meet other Japanese government and
business leaders.
</P>
<P>
As Britain holds the rotating presidency of the European Union
(EU) for six months from January, Blair and Hashimoto will also
hold an EU-Japan summit meeting Monday together with Jacques
Santer, president of the European Commission, the EU's executive
body.
</P>
<P>
During Blair's visit to Japan, the two countries will
officially inaugurate the 1998 British festival in Japan which aims
at introducing British culture to the Japanese people throughout
the year. 
</P>
