<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- the Philippines saw its export
earnings for November 1997 increasing by 24.7 percent from 1.85
billion U.S. dollars in November 1996 to 2.306 billion dollars,
data released by the Philippine National Statistics Office showed
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Cumulative receipts for the first 11 months of 1997 reached
22.995 billion dollars, up by 23.2 percent from 18.659 billion
dollars in 1996, according to the data.
</P>
<P>
However, the November figure represented a 0.9-percent drop
from the 2.326 billion dollars for October 1997.
</P>
<P>
Electronics and components, which earned 1.059 billion dollars
in November, had the biggest share of the total export receipts.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained the top market with receipts posting
a 32.4-percent growth in November to 789.65 million dollars from
596.16 million dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the continuing free-fall of the Philippine peso
has contributed to the better performance of the country's
exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
