<HEADLINE> 3 Southeast Asian Nations to Promote Growth Triangle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The three countries
involved in the Indonesia/Malaysia/Thailand-Growth Triangle
(IMT-GT) have agreed to contribute 70,000 U.S. dollars each to
promote and market the sub-region collectively, according to a
senior official Friday.
</P>
<P>
The money would be channeled to the Malaysia-Indonesia-Thailand
Tourist and Travel Association (MITTAS) by the end of this month
to be kept in a fund, MITTAS Chairman Syed Mohamad Aidid Syed
Murtaza said Friday in Pulau Pinang, northern Malaysia, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
The fund would only be used for the promotion and marketing of
the sub-region and the programs must be approved by the IMT-GT
Marketing and Promotion Task Force, said Syed Mohamad Aidid, who
is also chairman of the task force.
</P>
<P>
The fund would also be used for MITTAS' participation in
national and international travel fairs to be held in Singapore,
Malaysia, Indonesia and Thailand this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The official said it would also be used to finance tours in the
region by travel agents and media representatives from the
targeted countries and regions -- China, Singapore, Japan,
Australia, New Zealand, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said MITTAS would also produce uniform travel manuals and
maps for the sub-region for better impact.
</P>
<P>
A calendar of events for 1999 would also be produced and it
would incorporate events of the states and provinces of the
sub-region, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the first IMT-GT Friendship
Autoventure would be organized in June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
