<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Mexican Federal Roads Police (PFC)
confiscated a total of 59,964.313 kilograms of marijuana and
4,770.796 kilograms of cocaine during 1997, a communique revealed
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The PFC bulletin said that the seizures made last year are a
record compared to the last seven years, and a 32.7 percent
increase compared to 1996. (Mexico Drugs Seized) 
