<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Principal Tasks for China's Rural Development Outlined (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Central Rural Work
Conference was held in Beijing Jan. 7-9.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with conference participants in the Great Hall of
the People today, Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), said that China
would increase the output of farm produce, raise the annual income
of farmers and maintain a steady rural development despite the
difficulties it might encounter this year.
</P>
<P>
As the year 1998 is the first year to implement the principles
and policies made at the 15th National Congress of the CPC, there
are many arduous tasks ahead in reform, economic development and
social stability, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Last year's agricultural production was a good one after two
years of consecutive bumper harvest, paving the way for the
country's economic growth and social stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiang attributed the harvests to concerted efforts by farmers
under the leadership of Party committees and governments at all
levels as well as support from other trades. He also extended
cordial greetings to those working in the agricultural industry on
behalf of the CPC Central Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to guard against laxity after good harvests and
pay more attention to studying the changing situation and new
problems, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding problems in rural areas now include weak sales in
farm produce, a drop in prices and slower growth in farmers'
income, Jiang said, adding that they will hamper social stability
if China fails to find a timely and effective solution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
