<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Plans Annual Investment Fair in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, the capital of east
China's Fujian Province, will hold its annual international trade
and investment fair May 20-29.
</P>
<P>
The '98 Fuzhou International Trade and Investment Fair will
coincide with celebrations for the 2,200th anniversary of the
establishment of the city of Fuzhou, according to Vice Mayor Liu
Yongzhao.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature special workshops on investment,
agriculture, industry and transportation, real estate,
high-technology and tourism.
</P>
<P>
A city official said that overseas investment has become a
lifeline of the Fuzhou economy in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that overseas-funded enterprises
accounted for 66 percent of Fuzhou's industrial output and 88
percent of its exports last year.
</P>
<P>
The annual trade and investment fair has become a major venue
for Fuzhou to attract overseas capital and to create trade
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Last year contracts worth 2.09 billion U.S. dollars in total
investment and 1.85 billion U.S. dollars in foreign investment
were signed during a similar fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
