The U.S. defense secretary is scheduled to visit Thailand as a
guest of Prime Minister and Defense Minister Chuan Leekpai on
January 16 and 17, according to a press release of the U.S.
Information Service, available Friday.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will discuss security issues of mutual interest with
Chuan, Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan and other senior Thai
government and military officials.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is a stop of Cohen's seven-nation Asia trip, which
will also take him to Malaysia, Indonesia, Singapore, China, Japan
and South Korea.  
