<HEADLINE> Russia Edges Croatia in Men's Water Polo Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Russia pulled a major upset in the
opening day of the men's water polo competition by beating Olympic
silver medalist Croatia 6-4 at the world swimming championships
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Alexandre Evstigneev opened the account for Russia with an
extra-man goal after Ratko Stritof was ejected. Then Croatia hit
an equalizer through a penalty goal by Perica Bukic, the backbone
of the runner-up team in the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Bukic scored his second goal at 2:44 of the second quarter, but
Irek Zinnourov pulled it even nine seconds from half-time on the
extra after Vjekoslav Kobescak was sidelined for 20 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Nikolai Kozlov put Russia into lead again when he scored from
long range at 6:00, and 90 seconds later Evstigneev made it 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Croatia closed the gap at 1:10 as Igor Hinic scored a left-hand
catch position goal, and Hrvoje Herceg scored an underarm shot to
level the match at 4-4.
</P>
<P>
The fourth quarter went to Russia as Alexandre Erychov and
Dmitri Gorchkov scored one goal apiece to compete the victory.
</P>
</TEXT>
