<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's County-level Election Of People's Congress Deputies (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 9 (Xinhua) -- In Xiaoshan, a county-level
city in east China's Zhejiang Province, 910,000 people recently
voted to choose some of the 20,147 deputies to the city people's
congress.
</P>
<P>
One man, Lou Boying, said after making his choice, "The
state has given us the right to directly elect county people's
congress deputies, and we must cherish this opportunity and make
our best choice."
</P>
<P>
China started experimenting with the direct election of
deputies to the county-level people's congress in this coastal
province in 1979, when the country began its reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
Kong Xiangyou, vice-chairman of the Standing Ccommittee of the
Zhejiang Provincial People's Congress, has this to say, "The many
direct elections of deputies to the county-level people's congress
have improved people's awareness of democracy, and the common
people have a deeper understanding of the people's congress at the
grass-roots level."
</P>
<P>
According to provincial people's congress officials, about 90
percent of the candidates are chosen by a group of ten or more
common people, and government organizations submit the other 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
"This year's direct elections had a high rate of joint choices
by voters," said Zhao Yongqian, chairman of the Xiaoshan City
People's Congress.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Direct Election Of County-level People's Congress Deputies (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to Chinese laws, candidates whose names are submitted
by ordinary folk have the same rights as those submitted by
governmental organizations, so 2,350 of the 2,605 initial
candidates in Tongxiang City were suggested by ten or more voters.
</P>
<P>
"Initial candidates from county constituencies enthusiastically
participated in the election campaign," said Wang Jianrong,
vice-chairman of the Tongxiang City People's Congress, "and final
candidates even came from a primary in Wutong Township."
</P>
<P>
In addition to polling stations, there were many mobile ballot
boxes to get ballots from various families. In Tongxiang City,
2,470 mobile ballot boxes collected more than 20 percent of the
ballots.
</P>
<P>
Voters favor elections now more than 18 years ago, and as many
as 80 percent of the people vote, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
China is gradually standardizing the election process,
according to Zhong Xuequan of the NPC Standing Committee's General
Office.
</P>
<P>
The election of county-level people's congress deputies is the
first since the revision of the country's election law in 1995.
The deputies serve for five years.
</P>
<P>
By the first half of next year, the national, provincial, city
and county people's congresses will have 900,000 deputies from
across the country, according to NPC sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
