<HEADLINE> Tourism Growth in Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Hunan province received
40 million tourists in 1997, and its total revenues from tourism
reached eight billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Following the theme "1997 China Tourism Year," Hunan developed
four routes for tourists: Changsha-Zhangjiajie-Mengdonghe,
Changsha-Yueyang, Changsha-Shaoshan, and Changsha-Hengshan
Mountain.
</P>
<P>
