<HEADLINE> Kenyan Opposition DP to Take up Seats in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The opposition Democratic Party
of Kenya (DP) will take up its seats in the Eighth Parliament but
will not cooperate with the ruling Kenya African National Union
(KANU), the Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted DP Secretary General Joseph Munyao as saying
Thursday that his party was prepared to take up its role as the
Official Opposition in Parliament.
</P>
<P>
DP has got 39 elected members of parliament (MPs) and two
nominated MPs, making a total of 41 out of 222 MPs in Parliament
and gaining the status of the Official Opposition in Parliament.
</P>
<P>
"As the Official Opposition party in Parliament, we shall
maintain a democratic crusade without being blackmailed by the
'black sheep' among us," he said.
</P>
<P>
Munyao noted that DP was determined to push for comprehensive
legal and administrative reforms to pave way for free and fair
elections.
</P>
<P>
The opposition party maintained that its presidential
candidate, Mwai Kibaki, who got 1.9 million votes to President
Daniel arap Moi's 2.4 million votes, won the race but was denied
victory due to rigging by KANU.
</P>
<P>
The party official pointed out that a team of six lawyers was
collecting evidence to challenge President Moi's re-election in
court.
</P>
<P>
The Opposition National Development Party, Ford-Kenya, Safina
and religious groups which observered the elections have accepted
the outcome of the just-concluded General Election.
</P>
<P>
Another main opposition Social Democratic Party whose
presidential candidate is Charity Ngilu yesterday accepted the
final results of the elections. 
</P>
