<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Plans to Set Up 3 More EPZs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government is
planning to set up three more export processing zones (EPZs) in
the country to meet the increasing demand from domestic and
foreign investors, the national news agency BSS reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The new EPZs will be located respectively at Gazipur, 30
kilometers north of here, and Lamonirhat and Sirajganaj, 270 and
113 kilometers northwest of here, BSS quoted Moazzem Hossain Khan,
executive chairman of the Bangladesh Export Processing Zone
Authority, as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the three EPZs will begin after the development
work on the Comilla and Ishurdi EPZs, which are 140 kilometers
northwest and 90 kilometers southeast of here, is completed, the
chairman said. Work on the Comilla and Ishurdi zones is scheduled
to start in April this year.
</P>
<P>
The chairman said both local and foreign investors are showing
keen interest in making investment in the three newly planned
zones.
</P>
<P>
The existing two EPZs in Chittagong and Dhaka are unable to
cope with the increasing demand from investors, as 76 and 29
industrial units are already in operation and 56 and 43 others are
under implementation there.  
</P>
</TEXT>
