<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blast Kills 2 in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- An explosion ripped through a
warehouse in a province south of Manila, killing two people and
damaging several houses nearby, police said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the blast Thursday evening triggered fire which
razed the structures storing homemade dynamites in San Pedro,
Laguna Province.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the warehouse owner and his daughter,
respectively aged 48 and 24, were charred beyond recognition. The
glass windows and wooden panels of houses within a 500-meter
radius were shattered by the strong explosion.
</P>
<P>
Police said they recovered from the site blasting caps,
filaments and sodium cyanide being used to manufacture dynamites.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
