<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Citizen
</P>
<P>
-- Education Minister Sibusisu Bengu said yesterday teachers
in the country had to pull up their socks or be fired, saying the
government could not afford to pay salaries to teachers not
committed to teaching and who did not achieve what was expected
of them.
</P>
<P>
The Star
</P>
<P>
-- Anglo American, South Africa's mining giant, is facing a
three billion U.S. dollars lawsuit following charges by America
Mineral Fields, its U.S. rival, that it had "tortuously
interfered" with its contracts in the Democratic Republic of
Congo, the company sources said.
</P>
<P>
Business Day
</P>
<P>
-- Falling crude oil prices in the wake of recent Dollar
strength were expected to have a positive effect on South
Africa's fuel-dependent transport and agricultural sectors and on
inflation, a poll of oil analysts and economists said yesterday.
</P>
