<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Government Supports Hong Kong Policy on Asylum Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese central government
is supportive of the policy announcement Thursday by the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) government regarding the
termination of Hong Kong as the "port of first asylum." A decision
on the policy will be made through legal procedures.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said that the
policy of the HKSAR government on the proposed termination of Hong
Kong as the "port of first asylum" is in the interests of
maintaining prosperity and stability in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the policy, Shen said, an early and thorough
settlement is expected of the question of the Vietnamese boat
people and refugees remaining in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The policy should be beneficial to preventing an influx of
illegal Vietnamese immigrants into Hong Kong, Shen said, which
serves the interests of Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the Chinese central government will always support
the positive efforts made by the HKSAR government in resolving the
question of Vietnamese boat people and refugees remaining in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Shen said, "We also hope that the countries
and international organizations concerned will effectively perform
their duties in resettling and repatriating the Vietnamese boat
people and refugees still remaining in Hong Kong." This would put
an early end to the refugee problem that has plagued Hong Kong for
a long time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
