<HEADLINE> Sydney Customs Seizure Belongs to Coach Zhou Zhewen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 9 (Xinhua) -- A dozen vials of liquid which
customs officers at Sydney Airport found in the baggage of a
member of the Chinese swimming team belonged to coach Zhou Zhewen,
a Chinese official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
During a baggage examination on Thursday, customs officers
found in swimmer Yuan Yuan's hand baggage a thermos flask
containing a dozen vials of liquid.
</P>
<P>
"Zhou wanted to bring these vials to a friend," the official
said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team will hold a press conference later Friday.
