"It is my intention to invite Italian businessmen to explore
the possibility of direct investment in this market," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hasina said that Bangladesh and Italy can cooperate in trade,
investment and other economic fields for mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
As her country is a large market with a population of 120
million and the government has adopted an export-led growth
strategy, she invited the Italian business community to utilize
the favorable investment opportunities that Bangladesh offers.
</P>
<P>
The Italian prime minister, who arrived here after a three-day
visit to India, is scheduled to hold talks with Hasina and call on
President Shahabuddin Ahmed.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between the two countries in the previous
fiscal year ended June 30, 1997 was recorded at 257 million US
dollars, with Dhaka exporting 207 million dollars worth of
garments and leather products and importing 50 million dollars
worth of chemicals and machinery.  
