<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Bourses Drop Heavily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian stock market
crashed to a heavy drop Thursday following a historic low of the
rupiah (national currency), brokers here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah was traded at 11,000 per US dollar here Thursday, a
22 percent decline in a single day. The currency has lost about
300 percent of its value against the greenback since July last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Jakarta Stock Exchange composite price index fell 47.131
points from 394.239 to 347.108 points, a decrease of 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
The index of all individual sectors also dropped to a low
position. The biggest fall occurred at agricultural sector which
lost to 39 points.
</P>
<P>
Brokers attributed the drop of the stock market to investors'
confidence in the Indonesian economy. Investors were worried that
the steep drop in the rupiah would further worsen the already
ailing performance of most locally listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the fall of the rupiah to the worsening of
public confidence in the economy and the International Monetary
Fund's (IMF's) disappointment over the government's programs in
coping with the monetary crisis.
</P>
<P>
In October last year, Indonesia agreed on an IMF-led bailout of
over 30 billion dollars and committed to conduct a series of
reforms in the country in a bid to overcome the monetary crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
