<HEADLINE> Rusedski Reachs Quarterfinals in Qatar Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Greg Rusedski of Britain
advanced to the quarter-finals of the one million U.S. dollars
Qatar Open tennis Thursday by winning easily over Karim Alami of
Morocco 6-2, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski, the top seed after the withdrawal of the injured
Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia, beat Alami in just 67 minutes and
next play France's number eight seed Fabrice Santoro.
</P>
<P>
In other second round matches Thursday, third-seeded Fabrice
Santoro of France downed German Martin Sinner 6-3, 6-4, while
Sjeng Schalken of the Netherlands beat Carlos Costa of Spain 7-5,
2-6, 7-6 (7-5) in his second round match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
