<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Vocational Training Centers for Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has drawn up a plan to
increase its number of vocational training centers to 500 by the
year 2000, the Ministry of Vocational Training and Rural
Industries said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Currently there are 165 vocational training centers
countrywide, among which three are at national level, 11 district
level and 151 rural level.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics of the ministry showed that 10,613
trainees were enrolled by the Vocational Training Authority (VTA)
last year, 3.5 percent down from its average annual accommodation
of 11,000.
</P>
<P>
The VTA, however, plans to train 15,000 people this year and
increase its capacity to 25,000 by the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
