<HEADLINE> Albania to Establish Model Relations with Macedonia, Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Albania hopes to establish model
relations with Macedonia and Greece, which will do good to
regional peace and stability, Foreign Minister Paskal Milo said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Milo made the comment while announcing that Albanian Prime
Minister Fatos Nano will visit Macedonia between January 15-16.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of Nano's visit is to strengthen the bilateral
relations. His visit will improve the international cooperation in
the region," Milo said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that the two countries will sign nine
agreements during Nano's visit.
</P>
<P>
Albania and Macedonia signed six agreements when Macedonian
Foreign Minister Blagoj Handziski visited Albania last December.
</P>
</TEXT>
