<HEADLINE> Myanmar Strives for Advancement of Computer Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is planning to form a
central computer organization and associations of computer
amateurs, technicians and experts, and entrepreneurs this year to
strive for the development and advancement of computer technology
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Arrangements are also underway to issue related rules and
procedures following the promulgation of the Computer Technology
Development Law, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with local computer experts and entrepreneurs here
Thursday, Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace
and Development Council, urged them to join hands with the
government in the endeavors for the advancement and proper
application of computer technology.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also chairman of the Myanmar Computer
Science and Technology Development Council and the Education
Committee, also called for the proper use of the Internet to
prevent cultural problems.  
</P>
</TEXT>
