<HEADLINE> Value of Thailand's Rice Exports Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 9 (Xinhua) -- Higher prices and the lower baht
boosted the value of Thailand's rice exports last year by 29
percent over 1996 to 60.7 billion baht (1.23 billion US dollars),
according to the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Healthy exports were likely to continue this month and next to
meet orders mainly from Indonesia, Iran, the Philippines and
countries in Africa, Commerce Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi was
quoted Friday by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Rice Mills Association forecast that rice exports this
month will reach 430,000-450,000 tons and total exports for the
year will be at least 5.3 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
