<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Hands over Military Base to Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The United States reverted
its Quarry Heights military base to Panama on Thursday, which used
to be the headquarters of the U.S. Southern Command.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Ambassador William Hughes handed over the keys of the
military complex to Panamanian Foreign Minister Ricardo Alberto
Arias and to the Regional Interoceanic Authority (ARI) General
Administrator Nicolas Ardito Barletta.
</P>
<P>
The 27-hectare U.S. military base, located along the Panama
Canal, was built in 1914 for the operations of the U.S. Southern
Command in Latin America. The U.S. Southern Command was moved to
Miami in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
The handover of the Quarry Heights was a result of the
Torrijos-Carter treaty signed in 1977, which stipulated the return
of the Panama Canal and the delivery of the military installations
to the Central American country by December 1999.
</P>
<P>
There are 33 buildings with education installations, a barber
shop, a hotel and a restaurant in the military base which will be
turned into a diplomatic village. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980109.0278 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Population Decreases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The population of Ukraine was 50.5
million by January 1, 1998, 415,000 less than the previous year,
the Ukrainian news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Due to the sluggish economic situation and falling living
standard in Ukraine, which led to higher death rate and lower
birth rate, the country's population has decreased by 1.5 million
from 52 million before it announced independence in 1991, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Immigration is also anther factor of population fall, the
report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
