<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Oil Prices Hit 2-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan crude oil prices
registered the lowest quotation of the last two years, posting
13.07 dollars a barrel, said Petroleos de Venezuela (PDVSA)
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The restoration of Iraq's oil exports, middlemen, and the
excess supply lowered the prices of crude, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The drop in the quotation of the Venezuelan basket of crudes
was registered Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
PDVSA is now considering measures to contend with the price
drop because it could affect Venezuela's fiscal income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
