<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish Police Thwart Mass Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Spanish police foiled a mass
suicide planned by 32 members of a doomsday sect and arrested the
cult leader, officials said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Heide Fittkau-Garthe, a 57-year-old German psychologist, was
arrested late Wednesday on charges of attempting to incite others
to commit suicide.
</P>
<P>
Police said 32 members of a group called the Isis Holistic
Center planned to end their lives at a volcano on Tenerife, one of
the seven islands in the Canary archipelago.
</P>
<P>
The group, which may be linked to the infamous Solar Temple
suicide cult or a Hindu apocalyptic sect, was convinced the world
would end at 20:00 GMT on Thursday evening. The sect members
believed their bodies would be picked up by a spaceship and
transported to a new world.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 32 sect members planning to commit mass suicide,
including five children, were German nationals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
