<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, January 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI -- A road accident in central Kenya on Wednesday had
killed at least 54 people, the Kenya Television Network
(KTN) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened when a Stage Coach bus plunged off a
bridge into River Nithi in Chuka, Meru District, at 5:45 p.m. on
Wednesday. Forty-two people died on the spot, said the report,
adding the crash is one of the worst in recent years.
(Kenya-Road Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- A total of 480.7 kilograms of smuggled pure heroin
was seized in eastern Turkey Thursday, semi-official Anatolia News
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish police stopped and searched a passenger bus, which
came from Baku, capital of Azerbaijan, at the Sarp Border Gate on
the Turkey-Georgia border, and found the heroin in 470 parcels
hidden in the bus.
</P>
<P>
The police also detained the driver of the bus, according to
the news agency. (Turkey-Heroin-Seized)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Eighty percent of the adults in U.S. prisons are
locked up because of criminal activities linked to drug and
alcohol abuse, said a report from a group urging increased
spending on prison drug treatment programs.
</P>
<P>
The report by the National Center on Addiction and Substance
Abuse urged governments, particularly the states, to spend more
money to help 1.4 million inmates quit their habits before
returning to society. (US-Prisoner)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) Thursday
approved the sixth quarterly review of the economic development
and agreed to release an about 670 million U.S. dollar loan under
the Extended Fund Facility for Russia.
</P>
<P>
An IMF press statement noted that Russia's economic growth has
resumed, inflation has remained on a downward trend, and
structural reforms have gained renewed momentum. However, there is
some concern about progress in addressing the fiscal problem, in
particular low revenue collection. (IMF-Russia-Disbursement)
</P>
