<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Foreign Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan Minister of Foreign
Affairs Alvaro Ramos resigned from his portfolio, it was known
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ramos announced his decision the other day during a meeting
with President of the Republic Julio Maria Sanguinetti. Ramos had
met before with the President of the Board of the National Party,
Alberto Volonte.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the National Party, to which Ramos belongs,
explained that the foreign minister's resignation was due to
strictly personal reasons. Ramos has been out of the country for a
long time because of the delicate health of his wife.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that Ramos will also resign his seat in
the Senate and will use his time in party matters.
</P>
<P>
He will maintain his nomination to the presidency of the United
Nations General Assembly next September.
</P>
<P>
Ramos's resignation is the second in the coalition government
of Sanguinetti since the start of his mandate in 1995, and the
first of a minister belonging to the National Party. 
</P>
