<HEADLINE> Blair Says Britain to Play Constructive Role in EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said here today that Britain will play a constructive role in
European construction during its six-month European Union (EU)
presidency starting early this month.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after meeting with the 20
Commissioners of the EU Commission in London, Blair said that the
Labor government would seek a "strong and leading role in shaping
Europe's future."
</P>
<P>
"I have no doubt at all that we will show and demonstrate to
the whole of Europe the competence and constructive approach that
should mark any successful presidency," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
"In the months in which this new government has taken power in
Britain, there have been good and close relations with the
ministers and European Commissioners across a whole range of
issues," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, EU Commission President Jacques Santer
also expressed his optimism towards the British presidency.
</P>
<P>
"I am quite clear that Britain will do its utmost to play a
full and constructive role in making the launch of EMU (European
Monetary Union) a success," Santer said.
</P>
<P>
Santer noted that Europe also need "that same spirit of
dynamism, vigour and creativity that is once again the hallmark of
the United Kingdom today".
</P>
<P>
"I would like to say that this new positive approach the
British government is following on European issues is as
refreshing as it is highly appreciated," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
